touch - This command is used to create a file.
Syntax - touch <file_name>
 
Following are the commands related to touch which are as follows :-

1) To change the access time and modification time of a file - 
   Syntax - touch -a <file_name>
   
2) To change the only modification time of a file - 
   Syntax - touch -m <file_name>
   
3) To update time of File1 with respect to File2 -
   Syntax - touch -r <File1> <File2>
                     or 
            touch <File1> -r <File2>
         
4) To create non-empty file -
   Syntax - touch -c <file_name>
